  "source": "Analyses/Bivariate/CoincidentFrequencyAnalysis.cs @ fc28c0c -- X12 exact oracle, emitter-verified against the real RMC.BestFit CoincidentFrequencyAnalysis and reproduced bit-identically by the C++/R/Python runners. CFA consumes a fitted Normal-copula BivariateAnalysis (seeded DEMCzs) + a 5x5 additive response grid Z=X+Y and builds an AEP curve over 5 Z bins via the conditional-frequency law. The Z output bins (endpoint-inclusive linspace of the response) are deterministic: z_output == [-4,-2,0,2,4]. The z=0 bin is the exact symmetry point AEP == 0.5 (mode/mean/lower/upper), independent of the copula posterior. The rest of the AEP/mode/mean/CI curve depends on the copula-parameter posterior, which is CHAOTICALLY sensitive: the deterministic bivariate copula log-likelihood + MLE match C#/C++ to rel 1e-8 (fixtures/estimation/bivariate_smoke.json + the normal_copula CDF companion), but the 300-iteration seeded DEMCzs MAP diverges at ~1e-6 between the C# and C++ MersenneTwister streams (copula bivariate-normal-integration ULP differences amplified over the chain -- inherent, not a port bug; see docs/upstream-csharp-issues.md). So the curve is scoped to its deterministic invariants (z bins + z=0 symmetry point + curve_length == 5).",
